description:
Well I know taht we don't have end of the year and still have some time for register nice images.
ut last months I collected some better photos of our Solar System objects so I just need to update my small collage which I called "My Solar System"

Probably I'll udpate it once more at the end of 2020 :)

Photos of Jupiter and Mercury are from 2017, rest of photos from 2020.

Equipment and scopes:

Camera:  ZWO ASI 178 MM-C for all objects
Mount:   Sky-Watcher NEQ-6  for all objects

Sun:   Bresser Messier 152/1200 h-alpha mod, etalon from Lunt50THaPT
Mercury, Jupiter:   Truss Newtonian 400/1800 + barlow TV x2
Venus:   Astofaktoria Quartz D-K 190/3560
Rest of the planets:     Astofaktoria Newton 350/1400 + barlows Tele Vue 2x or 3x
title: My Solar System - AD 2020 update
